<h4 id="background">Background</h4>
<ol>
  <li>we have rigorously constructed three fundamental number systems:
    <ul>
      <li>The natural number system N, The integers Z and the rational Q.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

<h4 id="history">History</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Limit is a concept on one level is quite intuitive, but to pin down turn out
to be quite difficult</li>
  <li>Even the great mathematician Euler and Newton had difficult with this
concept. It was only until 19th century cauchy figure out how to deal with
this concept rigorously.</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="galois">Galois</h4>
<ol>
  <li>You are of course free to design you own number system, possibly including one
division by zero is plausible; but you will have to give up one of the axioms.</li>
